	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105837221062963>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Whos crappiest Sk?</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 16th 12:26 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=245498><span id=Sage>AdiemusFV</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>39 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.57]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Okay, point, counter-point, counter-counter-point. :)<br><br>First off, I've always chosen the Human race for my characters and am quite content with them. <b>Nothing</b> is going to change my mind unless one day SoE decides to permo-ban spell usage from Humans since they aren't considered magical blood. In anycase, personally, enjoyment of the character comes from the player themselves and NOT from what anyone else have to say. You can like what you have. Or you don't like it.<br><br>Stat-wise and ability-wise, the differences among each race <b>trivializes</b> as the career of the Shadow Knight progresses. The only clear and distinct advantage I see which would separate one race from the rest are the Ogre's racial invulnerabilty to being stunned in front.<br><br>But anyways, my third view:<br><br>FACTION - I believe this is a non-issue in later stages of the game, BUT can be a hassle to deal with for Iksars early on in their career. However, the Iksars do have a myriad of places available for them and traveling of course is no longer an issue now that PoK is available for everyone. As far as questing is concerned, the same sort of quest NPCs available for other races that are KoS to Iksars, can also be said for the same sort of quest NPCs available for Iksars but KoS to everyone else. Eventually everyone is going to need to work on their factions. I don't remember how difficult it was for an Iksar in Velious but...<br><br>STATS: STR and STA are the easiest statistics to improve upon IMO. That is why many melee classes have reached, are near, or have exceeded the caps on both. AGI and DEX on the other hand are two of the more difficult statistics (<b>not</b> that they are impossible) to improve for melee classes. <br><br>ARMOR PENALTY: Again, this is one of those that trivializes towards the latter stages of the gamer's career. The AC bonus would be great early on, but negligible in the end.<br><br>VISION: I agree with Rexz on this. Relying on spells is no big deal. You'd have to be lazy to consider a few clicks a hassle.<br><br>SWIMMING: Again, trivial for people who do not fight underwater. Still it is a very easy skill to build up. Simply auto-run towards a corner of a pool. Look up. Leave it on for the night, and presto.<br><br>GNOMES: I won't bother with this because quite frank, they look ridiculous enough. :)<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=680092 target=_new>Adiemus Aeternum</a>, <a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=724036 target=_new>Gaoler Loudbottom</a> - Firiona Vie</td></td></tr>
