	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>311 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.53]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Agree with most Adie.<br><br>ANY and ALL races can be made into an uber SHD.&nbsp;&nbsp;Its POINTLESS to get into a race argument, as I thought I was clear before.  NOOB_001 (see above), however, made some incorrect claims.<br><br>Few thoughts--<br><br>Faction--no--its basically pointless now.  If you can make it to the PoP or Luclin portal (PoP being VERY easy to get to nowadays), you can pretty much go ANYWHERE and XP.  IKS can hunt in Velious/Luclin/PoP pretty much as well as anyone else, so that is moot. <br><br>Re: quests--that *COULD* be a issue if the old, out-of-date Kunark stuff gives you a feeling of accomplishment and someone wanted to finish it.  With PoP out, however, many would just ignore doing a lot of Kunark quests, as they are items they would get they would pretty much bag anyways.<br><br>Re: stats--just because its easy to max out a stat or not does NOT necessarily mean that &quot;X&quot; stat is inheritly more important then another.  What it can mean, however, is where to emphasize putting your starting points into.<br><br>For instance, lets take Manslayer, who is, overall, the best SHD on Xev.  He is a DARK ELF and would, if he could start all over again, put ALL HIS POINTS INTO INT.  Why?  Because he had the hardest time maxing that out (he is unbuffed 305 now though).  Even he, however, would NOT say that INT is inheritly better then any other--they are ALL important.  Agruing otherwise is pointless.<br><br>Personally, at inception I WOULD pick STA or INT as the two stats that I would emphasize, but that has more to do with personal preference / difficulty of maxxing out certain stats moreso then one being inheritly more important than the other.  I put my starting points in STR (way back when...), and that was STUPID!!<br><br>Re: armor class--no--PoP HAS made AC relevant again.  Make no mistake about it.  Look it up on the Steel Warrior board.  Or, if you want to look noob like NOOB_001 above, go on the board and tell them that AC over 1250 is irrelevant.<br><br>Re: vision.  It doesnt matter if anyone that plays a vision-impaired class wants to admit it or not---NOT having at least basic infravision IS a drawback.  Furthermore, it CAN be easy to be of mid-to high level and NOT be wearing a vision-enhancing item.  Therefore, on RAIDS, you will find yourself NEEDING to scrap a good buff for a TURD vision buff.  Ive SEEN it happen--dont tell me it doesnt (nowadays, however, grp acumen is commonly cast...).<br><br>Gnomes as SHD--love em or hate em--they make TERRIFIC SHD..   =)<br><br>Luna<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Jul 16 13:56:48 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
